            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> Always included so it can be used reciprocally with `nvim_open_win()` or\r\n> `nvim_win_set_config()`. (otherwise the config of a window with `kWinStyleUnused`\r\n> will not unset the `kWinStyleMinimal` style of another window if passed to\r\n> `nvim_win_set_config()`, for example)\r\n\r\nThere are other side effects, though. For example, before this PR the following was possible:\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nlocal buf_id = vim.api.nvim_create_buf(false, true)\r\nlocal config = { relative = 'editor', row = 1, col = 1, height = 10, width = 10, style = 'minimal' }\r\nlocal win_id = vim.api.nvim_open_win(buf_id, true, config)\r\n\r\nvim.wo[win_id].cursorline = true\r\nvim.wo[win_id].number = true\r\n\r\n_G.adjust_pos = function()\r\n  local config = vim.api.nvim_win_get_config(0)\r\n  config.row, config.height = config.row + 1, config.height + 1\r\n  vim.api.nvim_win_set_config(0, config)\r\nend\r\n```\r\n\r\nSourcing this and executing `:lua adjust_pos()` will remove all set window-local options. Yes, without explicit `style = 'minimal'` it still works, but not setting it explicitly will open floating window with all *global* values of window-local options (like enabled 'number', 'cursorline', 'cursorcolumn', 'signcolumn', and many others). It can be fixed by explicitly setting `config.style = nil` in this snippet, but not sure if that is the right trade off.\r\n\r\nI wonder if the previous behavior was more versatile: require explicit `style='minimal'` in `nvim_win_set_config()` if needed. This implicitly keeps treating `style` as \"only initial config preset\".",
            "created_at": "2026-03-04T11:39:58Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/38122#issuecomment-3996994189",
            "id": 3996994189,
            "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/issues/38122",
            "node_id": "IC_kwDOAPphoM7uPUqN",
