                "url": "https://api.github.com/users/echasnovski",
                "user_view_type": "public"
            }
        },
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Responded on Matrix, but echoing for posterity:\r\n\r\n`style` doesn't only apply when initially opening/configuring a window, it's remembered and also applies when switching buffers.\r\n\r\nE.g: before this PR, switching buffers, then switching back would also reset local values to minimal (for options touched by the minimal style). It also has precedence over reused/global values. Makes sense for `nvim_win_get_config` to return it.\r\n\r\n> It can be fixed by explicitly setting `config.style = nil` in this snippet, but not sure if that is the right trade off.\r\n\r\nI kinda think this is fine, but if it causes too much friction I can compromise by just not re-applying in `nvim_win_set_config` if the new `style` is unchanged. (Though it'd still be possible for your local values to be clobbered if you switch buffers, like before)",
