        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> > It can be fixed by explicitly setting `config.style = nil` in this snippet, but not sure if that is the right trade off.\r\n> \r\n> I kinda think this is fine, but if it causes too much friction I can compromise by just not re-applying in `nvim_win_set_config` if the new `style` is unchanged. (Though it'd still be possible for your local values to be clobbered if you switch buffers, like before)\r\n\r\nI am also not *entirely* sure if forcing explicit `config.style=nil` is a bad thing, but it sure looks at least inconvenient and not intuitive. Maybe if documented more somewhere, it should be fine. Like in `nvim_win_set_config()` with \"Will always reapply `style`, if present\"?",
